libfame
------------------------------------------
libfame is a video encoding library. It can currently encode MPEG-1 and MPEG-4
rectangular video, as well as MPEG-4 video with arbitrary shape.

Runtime requirements:
  bash-5.2.21-1
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libfame-devel-0.9.1-1bl1
  libfame0.9.1-0.9.1-1bl1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-3
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.46-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://sourceforge.net/projects/fame/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/fame/libfame-0.9.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libfame-0.9.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libfame-0.9.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libfame-0.9.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfame-0.9.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfame0.9.1-0.9.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfame-devel-0.9.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

